latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Do you have a favourite movie? Probably a film that comes to your mind the moment someone asks you about you about your favourite film?

For me, it’s ‘Her’ - I watched it after a teacher from college recommend me to watch this and I’ve held it close to my heart since.

This movie answered a lot of questions I had myself, about my past relationships, and probably has helped me with a lot of issues I assume other people found within me, and issues I found within others but couldn't really put into words.

Inspired from the same, I wanted to work on a series capturing a lost lover in a city of dreams; a boy who seems to rejoice his solitude but can’t seem to settle without finding his love. 

Here’s a tribute to Spike Jonze, the director of the ‘Her’ featuring a beautiful conversation between Theodore & Samantha.

With @juhitaneja @mritunjay_badola7 @shankar.jangir05 @ben_wati  @makeupby_himanshi
Shot & Directed this video for @svaraprojects with the talented @delhidancer ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
A shoot close to my heart- inspired by the timeless beauty of Raja Ravi Varma’s women. The soft, diffused light, the open hair, the grace of draped sarees.

We wanted to capture that same stillness, that subtle drama in the eyes, that delicate balance of tradition and emotion. His work has inspired generations of artists, and this was our own quiet tribute.

Had the best time bringing this vision to life for @athyekaheritage with @juhitaneja @sheetal.saxena1 @sonakshisinghmehra @13moondust @heymanshe @hersheymakeup @akram_salmani_artist @augustine.production ♥️

latestPosts.caption:
Goa always brings something special to a shoot.. there’s so much character in the air here. The mix of Portuguese and Indian influence, the colours, the light, the faded textures; it all just adds so much depth.

Shooting this one for @studiorigu with @jahnvibansal, @varshagopall and @bansarichawada felt like everything aligned.

We shot in this beautiful Portuguese home (thanks to @tarinimanchanda) and wrapped up at the beach during golden hour. . Goa has this way of making even the simplest frames feel rich 🫶🏻

latestPosts.caption:
I first visited Jawahar Kala Kendra as a photography student back in 2016 for Jaipur Photo Festival - completely mesmerized by its architecture, geometry, and the sheer thought that had gone into every space.. thinking if I could ever shoot here.

Many years later, when we were planning this shoot, @jahnvibansal  suggested it as the location.. and it instantly felt right.
 @urvashikaur’s creations, with her beautiful textile and silhouettes, felt like a natural extension of the space.

As a photographer, I try to bring a new lighting approach to every shoot - that’s what keeps the process alive and exciting. Here, I played with both the ambient light and an editorial setup, letting the two worlds meet gently across textures and the structure.

A full circle moment in many ways.

Shot for @urvashikaur with @jahnvibansal @anaiina._ @animacreatives @makeupartist_bishu @___her.vision___ @shankar.jangir05

latestPosts.caption:
As a photographer, I try to approach each shoot with a fresh lighting language.. it’s what keeps the process exciting and alive for me. For this one, I blended the crispness of editorial light with warm, modulated patches that mimic sunlight filtering through leaves. The goal was to soften the architectural backdrop with something that felt quietly organic and intentional ❤️

Shot for @ogaanindia with @jahnvibansal @vanshika.singh_._ @ameliadsouza__ @yin.aien @___her.vision___ @radhikaahujaa @rashmi.singh.10485 @karmastudiodelhi
